    "Based on the first task of \"learning\" what a horse is based on its particular attributes as well as what black and white stripes are when described as a zebra (horse-like with black and white stripes), the model then infers that something resembling a horse with black and white stripes is a zebra.",
    "Most of the skepticism toward AI concerns what is often referred to as the \"black box\" problem (Castelvecchi 2016), and this skepticism is rightly warranted.",
    "Although the basic idea behind LLMs is the same, there is often very little information available about the specifics of different LLMs and the model's adjustable parameters.",
    "The fact that researchers cannot look \"under the hood\" into the specific details or decisions that the model makes is cause for concern and needs to be under consideration in any research endeavor.",
    "However, we argue that this issue can be overblown."
